      • parse

        TYPE parse​(XmlParsingContext parsingContext)
    throws BindingException
        This method is expected to parse content starting at the next event. Parsing will continue until the next event represents content that is not handled by this method.

        If isParsingStartElement() is true, then first event to parse will be the XMLStreamConstants.START_ELEMENT for the containing element. Otherwise, the first event to parse will be the first child of that XMLStreamConstants.START_ELEMENT.

        A JavaTypeAdapter is expected to parse until the peeked event is content that is not handled by this method. This also means that if isParsingStartElement() is true, then this method is expected to parse the END_ELEMENT event as well.

        Parameters:
        parsingContext - the XML parser and binding info
        Returns:
        the parsed value
        Throws:
        BindingException - if a parsing error occurs
